{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, mixtures containing (HFFA) combined with Class F FA at replacement levels of 5% to 15% show a reduction in flowability by 15% at a 10% replacement and by 25% at a 15% replacement level According to Georgiou [59].",
    "According to the data summarized in Table 3, the inclusion of FA as an SCM affects the fresh, mechanical, and durability properties of concrete.",
    "Rice husk ash (RHA)As shown in Table 4, Saand et al. [60] found that adding RHA at levels between 2.5% and 15% by weight decreases workability while increasing density by 5.02% at a 10% replacement level.",
    "Similarly, Kanthe et al. [61] observed that higher RHA content results in reduced workability, with a slump reduction of up to 12% when superplasticizers are not used.",
    "However, the use of superplasticizers significantly improves workability even at higher RHA levels."
  ]
}